description:
Sarah Gonzalez, was Daddy's little girl and she shares about her journey of the joyful relationship she had with her dad in her early childhood years as she walked along side him as he served as Chaplain of Cook County Jail, after his recovery from being an ex-offender who was addicted to drugs. He came to Chicago upon his release from prison in California, and had a heart for inmates.  

However, at the age of 6, the pain of seeing her dad die left her in a deep state of dispair and doubt. Sarah shares what happened in the years that followed her dad's death and how the devil tried to destroy her as she rebelled against anything having to do with God and Christianity. She got involved in the darkside which appeared to be a false light and started to see results that she could control her future and have good things happen!  But then something happened that terrified her.  A powerful True Story.
